<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3948] Replacing method on ExpandoMetaClass doesn&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3948</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Expando.metaClass.foo={-&amp;gt; def directBar=delegate.bar()
    println &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;directBar=${directBar}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;    
    def invokedBar=delegate.invokeMethod(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bar&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
    println &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;invokedBar=$invokedBar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
}

e=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Expando()
e.metaClass.bar={-&amp;gt;1}
e.foo()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//directBar=1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//invokedBar=1
&lt;/span&gt;
e.metaClass.bar={-&amp;gt;2}
e.foo()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//directBar=1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//invokedBar=2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for some reason delegate.bar() != delegate.invokeMethod(&apos;bar&apos;,null)&lt;br/&gt;
looks like at the direct call the closure got cached ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if the previous example continues with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;x=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Expando()
x.metaClass.bar={-&amp;gt;3}
e.foo()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//directBar=2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//invokedBar=2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;creating the new &apos;x&apos; object has side effect on the &apos;e&apos; objects metaclass?&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
